<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1252,1555]" box="[160,480,1252,1278]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,480,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Justification of the transfer</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1252,1555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[503,563,1287,1312]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[612,765,1287,1312]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis">
<emphasis box="[612,765,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">S. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it lacks diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[289,386,1322,1347]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,386,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Sergiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see previous paragraph on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[715,938,1322,1347]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis">
<emphasis box="[715,938,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">H. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but has all of the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[406,485,1357,1382]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,485,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in the case of previous species (compare 
<figureCitation box="[975,1068,1357,1382]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1375,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-75@11.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 6. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18), male allotype and female paratype of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a) holotype female habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(c) allotype male habitus, dorsal view.(d) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(e) paratype female habitus, dorsal view. (f) epigyne of the same, ventral view. (g–i) labels from type bottles. Scale bars a, c, e = 2 mm; b, d = 0.5 mm; f = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405201/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(b,d,f), 7 (d–e) with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kamura T" box="[278,425,1391,1416]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref7382" refString="Kamura T. 1992. Two new genera of the family Gnaphosidae (Araneae) from Japan. Acta Arachnologica. 41: 119 - 132. doi: 10.2476 / asjaa. 41.119." type="journal article" year="1992">Kamura 1992</bibRefCitation>
, figs 11, 16, 20, 25). Additionally, the male pedipalp of this species possesses an apico-ventral process bearing tuft of setae similar to that illustrated for 
<taxonomicName authority="Sankaran &amp; Sebastian, 2018" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2018" box="[160,669,1461,1486]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procula">
<emphasis box="[160,333,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Hitobia procula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sankaran PM &amp; Sebastian PA" box="[345,669,1461,1486]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" pagination="1733 - 1744" refId="ref7947" refString="Sankaran PM, Sebastian PA. 2018. New species of gnaphosid spiders (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from the Western Ghats of India. J Nat Hist. 52: 1733 - 1744. doi: 10.1080 / 00222933.2018.1478998." type="journal article" year="2018">Sankaran &amp; Sebastian, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[799,896,1461,1486]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a) with 
<bibRefCitation author="Sankaran PM &amp; Sebastian PA" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" pagination="1733 - 1744" refId="ref7947" refString="Sankaran PM, Sebastian PA. 2018. New species of gnaphosid spiders (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from the Western Ghats of India. J Nat Hist. 52: 1733 - 1744. doi: 10.1080 / 00222933.2018.1478998." type="journal article" year="2018">Sankaran and Sebastian 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2b–c). Based on these observations, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[160,307,1530,1555]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis">
<emphasis box="[160,307,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">S. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[346,425,1530,1555]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[346,425,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="2852" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1598,1728]" box="[160,276,1598,1624]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1598,1728]" lastBlockId="14.[160,1156,142,306]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="2852" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[268,423,1634,1659]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[268,423,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[434,562,1634,1659]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from the males of all known congeners by a prominent apico-ventral process of tibia bearing tuft of setae and a broad tegular apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[378,473,1703,1728]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Females are closely related to the females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin, Peng, Gong &amp; Kim, 1996" authorityName="Yin, Peng, Gong &amp; Kim" authorityYear="1996" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="2852" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monsta">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="2852" pageId="13" pageNumber="2851">Hitobia monsta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yin CM &amp; Peng XJ &amp; Gong LS &amp; Kim JP" box="[254,601,142,167]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" pagination="47 - 54" refId="ref8283" refString="Yin CM, Peng XJ, Gong LS, Kim JP. 1996. Description of three new species of the genus Hitobia (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from China. Korean Arachnol. 12: 47 - 54." type="journal article" year="1996">Yin, Peng, Gong &amp; Kim, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
having similar shape of spermathecae and an inverted triangular epigynal hood, but can be distinguished from the latter by the position of the epigynal hood, which is medially placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[807,958,212,237]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis">
<emphasis box="[807,958,212,237]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while it is placed near the posterior epigynal border in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin, Peng, Gong &amp; Kim" authorityYear="1996" box="[587,699,246,271]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monsta">
<emphasis box="[587,699,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">H. monsta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[821,915,246,271]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(d–e) with 
<bibRefCitation author="Song DX &amp; Zhu MS &amp; Zhang F" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" pagination="362" refId="ref8058" refString="Song DX, Zhu MS, Zhang F. 2004. Fauna Sinica: Invertebrata. Vol. 39, Arachnida: Araneae: Gnaphosidae. Beijing: Science Press; p. 362." type="book chapter" year="2004">Song et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 88A–B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[159,1156,365,1154]" box="[160,478,365,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,478,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Supplementary description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[159,1156,365,1154]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">
<emphasis box="[160,212,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[234,326,401,426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">allotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[345,445,401,426]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1375,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-75@11.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 6. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18), male allotype and female paratype of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a) holotype female habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(c) allotype male habitus, dorsal view.(d) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(e) paratype female habitus, dorsal view. (f) epigyne of the same, ventral view. (g–i) labels from type bottles. Scale bars a, c, e = 2 mm; b, d = 0.5 mm; f = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405201/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(c–d)). Body length 6.13. Prosoma length 3.06, width 2.31. Opisthosoma length 3.07, width 2.27. Eye sizes and interdistances: ALE 0.13. AME 0.14. PLE 0.12.PME 0.11; AME–AME 0.06. AME–PME 0.16.PME–PLE 0.12. PME–PME 0.13. Length of chelicerae 0.80. Clypeus height at ALEs 0.10, at AMEs 0.12. Measurements of pedipalp and legs. Pedipalp (right) 2.47 [0.92, 0.38, 0.31, 0.86], I (right) 7.52 [2.30, 1.28, 1.64, 1.49, 0.81], II (right) 7.38 [2.21, 1.24, 1.67, 1.46, 0.80], III 7.15 [2.02, 1.08, 1.41, 1.69, 0.95], IV 8.91 [2.42, 1.22, 1.98, 2.32, 0.97]. Leg formula: 4123. 
<emphasis box="[543,635,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Pedipalp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[647,736,609,634]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–c)): tibia disto-ventrally with a short, broad process bearing tuft of setae (
<figureCitation box="[572,664,644,669]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a)). Retrolateral tibial apophysis moderately long, flat, with inwardly directed pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[713,807,678,703]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–c)). Conductor short, widely triangular,arising apically from tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[604,692,713,738]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Tegulum with a short, wide,pointed apico-prolateral membranous tegular process (
<figureCitation box="[680,770,748,773]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a)). Tegular apophysis short, wide, apico-retrolateral in origin, lying close to the base of conductor and embolus (
<figureCitation box="[999,1087,782,807]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Embolus short, spine-like, arising disto-prolaterally from tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[887,976,817,842]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(a)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[159,1156,365,1154]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">
<emphasis box="[192,267,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[285,385,852,877]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[399,493,852,877]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1375,1398]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-75@11.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 6. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18), male allotype and female paratype of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a) holotype female habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(c) allotype male habitus, dorsal view.(d) eyes of the same, dorsal view.(e) paratype female habitus, dorsal view. (f) epigyne of the same, ventral view. (g–i) labels from type bottles. Scale bars a, c, e = 2 mm; b, d = 0.5 mm; f = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405201/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Body length 9.45. Prosoma length 4.49, width 3.28. Opisthosoma length 4.96, width 2.56. Eye sizes and interdistances: ALE 0.16. AME 0.17. PLE 0.16. PME 0.15; AME–AME 0.12. AME–PME 0.23. PME–PLE 0.19. PME–PME 0.18. Length of chelicerae 1.22.Clypeus height at ALEs 0.14,at AMEs 0.19.Measurements of palp and legs.Palp (right) 3.54 [1.21, 0.66, 0.55, 1.12], I – [2.89, –, –, –, –], II 8.74 [2.58, 1.64, 1.82, 1.77, 0.93], III (right) 8.80 [2.46, 1.48,1.61, 2.10,1.15], IV (right) 10.94 [3.12,1.68,2.31,2.72,1.11]. 
<emphasis box="[941,1022,1025,1050]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Epigyne</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1034,1121,1025,1050]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(d– e)): epigynal plate moderately sclerotised, with a wide antero-median hood, with crescent-like posterior epigynal margin (
<figureCitation box="[453,541,1094,1119]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(d)). Copulatory openings small, lying distantly from each other. Spermathecae large sac-like. (
<figureCitation box="[547,635,1129,1154]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(e)). Fertilisation ducts narrow, diverging.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[159,1155,1213,1482]" box="[160,262,1213,1239]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[159,1155,1213,1482]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">
The ZSI collection has three glass bottles for this species.First bottle labelled as ‘holotype’ (5049/ 18) contains 
<specimenCount box="[294,414,1284,1309]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen in fairly good condition, with broken legs, almost detached opisthosoma and intact epigyne. Second bottle labelled as ‘paratype’ (no register number) contains 
<specimenCount box="[257,394,1353,1378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" type="female">three female</specimenCount>
specimens in fairly good condition, with broken legs. The epigyne of one of these specimens was found removed, but not kept in the tube. Third bottle labelled as ‘allotype’ (no register number) contains 
<specimenCount box="[573,666,1422,1447]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852" type="male">10 males</specimenCount>
in good condition, with broken legs. The same bottle has a small glass vial containing the dissected left pedipalp of one of the 
<typeStatus box="[997,1081,1457,1482]" pageId="14" pageNumber="2852">allotype</typeStatus>
males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
